<a href="http://www.hirebridge.com/v3/Jobs/JobDetails.aspx?cid=7531&amp;jid=306350" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i349.photobucket.com/albums/q362/Bri_Parsonnet/Hiring-Ad_Manager_Morningside-01_zpskqr08udf.jpg" border="0" alt=" photo Hiring-Ad_Manager_Morningside-01_zpskqr08udf.jpg"></a>
<br>
<font size="3" face="Futura MD Bt"><b> Now hiring Restaurant Managers for NEW Shake Shack Morningside Heights!</b>
<br>
<br>
Shake Shack is a modern day "roadside" burger stand serving deliciously classic burgers, fries, hot dogs, frozen custard, beer, wine, and more. With our fresh, simple, high-quality food at a great value, Shake Shack is a fun and lively community-gathering place unlike any other. Beginning in NYC, Shake Shack was founded by Danny Meyer's Union Square Hospitality Group, and moved out of the family in 2015 to become a publicly traded company. We are experiencing tremendous growth, and are looking for natural leaders who can help drive our continued success. <br>
<br>
We are currently seeking a Restaurant Manager to join our team. We bring together caring, warm, fun, and intelligent people who love to serve, and who embody our mission to Stand For Something Good. This is an excellent career growth opportunity for a food service professional with 2-3 years of management experience and a desire to learn, grow, and lead others.<br>
<br>
As a manager, you will be responsible for leading and driving the daily operations of your Shack location and oversee the kitchen and dining spaces to ensure a positive guest experience. You will be responsible for leading our Team Members, Team Leaders and Trainers, and championing our culture in your local community. To help you get there, our training programs provide the tools you need for success combined with hands on application of all manager functions. Not to mention, we have a ton of fun! <br>
<br>
<b>What You'll Need:</b><br>
- 2-3 years of Restaurant Management experience in a high-volume and fast paced environment <br>
- Warm, caring and positive attitude that drives hospitality and inspires others to do so<br>
- An aptitude for learning, coaching and driving excellence at all levels <br>
- A desire to learn and train others on all aspects of Shake Shack operations<br>
- Broad understanding of financial aspects of the business<br>
- Open, flexible availability <br>
<br>
<b>What You'll Do:</b><br>
- Manage all functions of our daily checklist and shift operations<br>
- Drive excellence and standards with inventory, quality and safety<br>
- Train, lead and develop our team to achieve excellence in guest experience and hospitality<br>
- Handle payroll, scheduling and labor management<br>
- Facility and equipment management<br>
- Fostering positive relationships between Shake Shack and the community<br>
<br>
<b>Our Benefits:</b><br>
- 401k plan with company match<br>
- Competitive salary and bonus plans<br>
- Professional Career Development<br>
- Flexible Spending Accounts and Transit benefits<br>
- Employee dining discounts<br>
- Online learning platform to support professional and team development<br>
<br>

<b>We participate in E-verify and are an equal opportunity employer</b><br>

